{
  "doc_id": "30133",
  "text": "Diagnosis of FSHD2 can be problematic, with no diagnostic short 4q D4Z4 array it can be misdiagnosed as a form of limb-girdle myopathy [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] . Sequencing of SMCHD1 has been used to confirm diagnosis in some cases [CITATION_3] [CITATION_4] , but this can be challenging as it is a large gene with 48 exons [CITATION_5] and most mutations appear to be private [CITATION_6] . Genetic heterogeneity also seems likely in FSHD2, although no locus apart from SMCHD1 has yet been identified.",
